Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE, as the exclusive marketing agent for 67/67A Serangoon Garden Way (“the Property”) is pleased to offer you the opportunity to purchase a 2 storey corner shophouse at the heart of Serangoon Garden with prominent main road frontage along Serangoon Garden Way and Serangoon Circus via a Public Tender exercise. 
Serangoon Garden is a charming rustic private landed housing estate. The estate is home to affluent and successful locals who choose to design and build their own homes. Some locational attributes include proximity to amenities and excellent accessibility to other parts of the island makes it highly desirable address for home. Most recently with Australian and French International schools there is a growing presence of expatriates. At the heart of Serangoon Garden, is Serangoon Garden Circus and Serangoon Garden Way which is a bustling commercial strip of 69 shophouses. Prominent landmarks in the area include Chomp Chomp Food Centre, Serangoon Garden Market & Food Centre, neighborhood Shopping Mall MyVillage, Food and Beverage Outlets, Clinics and lifestyle services.

The development comes with public carparking facility conveniently situated right in front of the unit. The Property is strategically located within a 13 minutes’ walk to the future Tavistock MRT Station, which is slated for completion in 2029. Prominent landmarks in the area include Chomp Chomp Food Centre, Serangoon Garden Market, myVillage at Serangoon Garden, Serangoon Gardens Country Club and the French and Australian International School.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
The Property will be tenanted to a bank, offering the prospective purchaser immediate rental income. In the longer term, the Property offers multiple flexible usages for the prospective purchaser to explore, including F&B, healthcare/medical, educational, showroom, retail, fitness centre, home & living and lifestyle businesses etc. Given the prime frontage of the commercial unit, the prospective purchaser can expect to unlock further capital values and enjoy a rental upside in the future. 

The Public Tender exercise closes at
7th May 2021 Friday, 3:00 pm

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: Prime Dual Frontage 999 Yr Shophouse in the Heart of Serangoon Garden

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text:
As one of Singapore’s most iconic neighborhoods that is designated as the first “Heritage Town” in 2011, East Coast / Joo Chiat is characterized by a mix of colorful shophouses of Peranakan (Straitsborn people of Chinese and Malay/Indonesian heritage) heritage that house popular F&B shops, trendy bars and hipster cafes. 

Much of the district’s charm comes from its historical heritage as a Peranakan enclave that has been beautifully retained, which juxtaposes a trendy vibe with restaurants, cool cafes and bars and hipster boutiques. The area is not only popular among locals and the nearby office crowd during daytime, it also transforms into a vibrant district by night time, frequented by after-work crowds, tourists and
residents. Some of the well-known F&B establishments at this bustling lifestyle destination include Madnest, Beach Road Prawn Mee Eating House, Penny University Artisanal Café and Al Forno (East Coast Road).

The Property is prominently located near to the junction of East Coast Road and Telok Kurau Road and falls within the Joo Chiat Conservation Area of high density commercial and residential developments. The immediate vicinity is home to a mix of old and new commercial businesses, conservation houses, hotels as well as numerous eateries, markets and shopping malls, which contributes to the bustling
area. By virtue of the seamless connectivity to the surrounding precincts, the Property is able to tap onto the residential catchment of Joo Chiat / East Coast residential enclaves, underpinned by a multitude of residents.

The Property is about 5 minutes’ drive to Eunos MRT (EW7) and Kembangan MRT (EW6) as well as future Marine Terrace MRT (TE27). It is also easily connected to other parts of the island via major arterial roads and expressways such as the East Coast Expressway (ECP), Pan Island Expressway (PIE) and Kallang-Paya Lebar Expressway (KPE), etc.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Sitting on a rectangular plot with a site area of approx. 2,380 sq ft, the Property enjoys
approx. 10 metres of frontage along East Coast Road and has a depth of approx. 23
metres. By conserving the front façade of the shophouse, there is an option to increase
the floor area from the existing 3,960 sq ft to 7,140 sq ft by constructing a new rear
extension of up to 5 storeys.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: A Pair Of Conservation Freehold Shophouses With Value-Add Potential (Virtual tour available)
